.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "September 2025" "Holberton School" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic UNIX command line interpreter that reads commands from
standard input and executes them.

The shell displays a prompt, waits for the user to enter a command,
and executes the command using the execve system call.

The command line consists of a single word with no arguments.

.SH FEATURES
- Displays a prompt and waits for user input
- Executes commands using execve
- Handles end of file condition (Ctrl+D)
- Prints error messages when commands are not found
- Works in interactive and non-interactive mode

.SH LIMITATIONS
This shell does not support:
- Command arguments
- PATH resolution
- Built-in commands
- Pipes, redirections, or special characters

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
file1 file2
($)
.fi

Non-interactive mode:
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
file1 file2
.fi

